---
import MarketingLayout from '../layouts/MarketingLayout.astro';
---
<MarketingLayout title="Websites for Local Businesses | Website Factory" description="Productized static websites for local businesses that need calls, trust, and speed.">
  <section class="hero-section">
    <div class="container hero-grid">
      <div>
        <p class="eyebrow">Websites for local businesses that need calls, trust, and speed</p>
        <h1>A practical website offer for owners who need a stronger online presence fast.</h1>
        <p>We turn your intake into a polished static site with clear service messaging, trust proof, and a direct call-to-action flow. No CMS overhead, no plugin maintenance.</p>
        <div class="cta-row">
          <a class="button-primary" href="/offer-site/contact">Start Project Intake</a>
          <a class="button-secondary" href="/offer-site/examples">See examples</a>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="panel">
        <h2>What this solves</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>Outdated sites that don’t build trust</li>
          <li>Slow pages that lose mobile visitors</li>
          <li>Vague offers that fail to convert calls</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="content-section">
    <div class="container card-grid">
      <article class="card"><h3>Starter Website</h3><p>Core 5-page site for credible launch and local lead capture.</p></article>
      <article class="card"><h3>Professional Website</h3><p>Expanded content, stronger proof sections, and more conversion detail.</p></article>
      <article class="card"><h3>Monthly Care</h3><p>Ongoing updates, content edits, and support after launch.</p></article>
    </div>
  </section>


  <section class="content-section">
    <div class="container comparison-section">
      <p class="eyebrow">Starter Site vs. Professional Launch</p>
      <h2>Starter gets you online credibly. Professional helps customers understand, trust, and choose you.</h2>
      <p class="comparison-intro">If you need a premium web presence fast, Starter is the right move. If you need your website to explain higher-value work and reduce buyer hesitation, Professional is built for that job.</p>
      <div class="comparison-grid">
        <article class="comparison-card starter">
          <h3>Starter Website</h3>
          <p>Best for businesses that need a clean, credible web presence quickly.</p>
          <ul>
            <li>4–5 core pages</li>
            <li>Basic service descriptions</li>
            <li>Mobile-friendly layout</li>
            <li>Contact page and clear call-to-action</li>
            <li>Basic local SEO structure</li>
            <li>Simple trust and credibility layout</li>
          </ul>
        </article>
        <article class="comparison-card professional">
          <h3>Professional Website Launch</h3>
          <p>Best for businesses that need the site to explain, persuade, and build trust.</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Expanded service copy</li>
            <li>Stronger homepage positioning</li>
            <li>FAQs that answer customer objections</li>
            <li>Testimonials or proof sections</li>
            <li>Gallery or before/after structure</li>
            <li>Service-area messaging</li>
            <li>More polished conversion flow</li>
            <li>Better fit for higher-value services</li>
          </ul>
        </article>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="content-section muted-bg">
    <div class="container two-col">
      <div>
        <h2>Why static websites?</h2>
        <p>Static sites are fast, secure, and low-maintenance. They eliminate common plugin vulnerabilities and reduce moving parts, which makes them reliable for busy owners.</p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <h2>Built for local SEO basics</h2>
        <p>Every site includes clear location/service structure, semantic headings, metadata, and conversion-focused page hierarchy so prospects and search engines understand your offer.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</MarketingLayout>
